     "## Build Knowledge Graph\n",
     "\n",
     "**What:** Setting up the knowledge graph storage (Neo4j or in-memory fallback).\n",
     "\n",
     "**Why:** Neo4j is the most popular graph database, but for this demo we use an in-memory representation.\n",
     "\n",
     "## Storage Options\n",
     "\n",
     "| Option | Pros | Cons |\n",
     "|--------|-----|------|\n",
     "| **Neo4j** | Persistent, scalable, queryable | Requires setup |\n",
     "| **In-memory** | Easy to run, no setup | Lost on restart |\n",
     "| **NetworkX** | Python-native | Small scale only |\n",
     "\n",
     "> **Production Tip:** For production, use Neo4j Aura (cloud) or self-hosted Neo4j. Set `NEO4J_PASSWORD` environment variable."
    ]
   },
