     "## Hybrid Retrieval Implementation\n",
     "\n",
     "**What:** Combining vector search (semantic similarity) with graph traversal (relationship-based).\n",
     "\n",
     "**Why:** Each approach has strengths:\n",
     "\n",
     "| Method | Strength | Weakness |\n",
     "|--------|----------|----------|\n",
     "| **Vector Search** | Finds semantically similar content | Misses relationships |\n",
     "| **Graph Traversal** | Understands entity connections | Needs structured entities |\n",
     "\n",
     "## How Hybrid Retrieval Works\n",
     "\n",
     "1. **Entity Extraction** - Identify entities in the user's question\n",
     "2. **Vector Retrieval** - Find documents similar to the query\n",
     "3. **Graph Retrieval** - Find entities + their relationships\n",
     "4. **Combine Results** - Merge and deduplicate\n",
     "\n",
     "## Entity Extraction\n",
     "\n",
     "The system uses the LLM to identify main entities from questions like:\n",
     "\n",
     "- \"Who founded Apple?\" → [Apple, Steve Jobs]\n",
     "- \"What products does Apple make?\" → [Apple, products]\n",
     "\n",
     "> This enables the graph to return relationship info like \"Apple PRODUCES iPhone\" which vector search alone would miss."
    ]
   },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Vector store created\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from langchain_community.vectorstores import Chroma\n",
    "from langchain_ollama import OllamaEmbeddings\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create vector store\n",
    "embeddings = OllamaEmbeddings(model=\"nomic-embed-text\")\n",
    "vectorstore = Chroma.from_documents(sample_docs, embeddings)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Vector store created\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Hybrid retriever ready\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Hybrid retriever class - combines vector and graph retrieval\n",
    "class HybridKGRetriever:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Combines vector and graph retrieval.\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, vectorstore, llm, graph_documents=None, k=4):\n",
    "        self.vectorstore = vectorstore\n",
    "        self.llm = llm\n",
    "        self.graph_documents = graph_documents or []\n",
    "        self.k = k\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def retrieve(self, query: str, k: int = None):\n",
    "        if k is None:\n",
    "            k = self.k\n",
    "        \n",
    "        vector_results = self.vectorstore.similarity_search(query, k=k)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        entities = self._extract_entities(query)\n",
    "        graph_results = self._graph_retrieve(query, entities)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        combined = vector_results + graph_results\n",
    "        return combined[:k]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _extract_entities(self, query: str) -> list:\n",
    "        prompt = f\"Extract main entity names from this question. Return comma-separated list. Question: {query}\"\n",
    "        result = self.llm.invoke(prompt)\n",
    "        entities = [e.strip() for e in result.content.split(\",\") if e.strip()]\n",
    "        return entities\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _graph_retrieve(self, query: str, entities: list):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Direct lookup: find entities in graph and return their relationships.\"\"\"\n",
    "        from langchain_core.documents import Document\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if not self.graph_documents or not entities:\n",
    "            return []\n",
    "        \n",
    "        results = []\n",
    "        query_lower = query.lower()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Find entities in query and get their relationships\n",
    "        for entity in entities:\n",
    "            entity_lower = entity.lower()\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Check if entity appears in query\n",
    "            if entity_lower in query_lower:\n",
    "                # Find matching node in graph\n",
    "                for graph_doc in self.graph_documents:\n",
    "                    for node in graph_doc.nodes:\n",
    "                        if entity_lower in node.id.lower():\n",
    "                            # Get all relationships for this node\n",
    "                            for rel in graph_doc.relationships:\n",
    "                                if rel.source.id == node.id or rel.target.id == node.id:\n",
    "                                    text = f\"{rel.source.id} {rel.type} {rel.target.id}\"\n",
    "                                    doc = Document(page_content=text, metadata={\"source\": \"knowledge_graph\", \"entity\": node.id})\n",
    "                                    results.append(doc)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return results\n",
    "\n",
    "retriever = HybridKGRetriever(vectorstore, llm, graph_documents=graph_documents, k=4)\n",
    "print(\"Hybrid retriever ready\")\n"
   ]
  },
